-\n1130-\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n1131-\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(workflows)\n1132-}\n1133-\n1134:func (h *Handler) handleAPIStepContent(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n1135-\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n1136-\tif !ok {\n1137-\t\treturn\n1138-\t}\n1139-\tworkflowName := r.PathValue(\"workflow\")\n1140-\tstepName := r.PathValue(\"step\")\n1141-\n1142-\t// Find the workflow file\n1143-\tclocheDir := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\")\n1144-\tvar wf *domain.Workflow\n1145-\tentries, _ := os.ReadDir(clocheDir)\n1146-\tfor _, e := range entries {\n1147-\t\tif e.IsDir() || !strings.HasSuffix(e.Name(), \".cloche\") || e.Name() == \"host.cloche\" {\n1148-\t\t\tcontinue\n1149-\t\t}\n1150-\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(clocheDir, e.Name()))\n1151-\t\tif err != nil {\n1152-\t\t\tcontinue\n1153-\t\t}\n1154-\t\tparsed, err := dsl.Parse(string(data))"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018kVm9VM4TvBwPKughR6bnn","session_id":"044f0678-c89a-4054-98f9-8679665edf9d","uuid":"42e8db9f-113a-4c40-bea8-77399a729cee"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"a3f6de09eb7da1f00","tool_use_id":"toolu_018kVm9VM4TvBwPKughR6bnn","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Find workflow view code","usage":{"total_tokens":57499,"tool_uses":19,"duration_ms":22727},"uuid":"4d5cf863-b267-4f70-98c9-ee38a82c31f3","session_id":"044f0678-c89a-4054-98f9-8679665edf9d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018kVm9VM4TvBwPKughR6bnn","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive summary of the findings.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've found all the code related to the workflow view and step details functionality. Here are the key findings:\n\n### Web UI Templates\n\n**Main workflow visualization template:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - This is the **primary file** where the workflow DAG visualization occurs with step detail drawer functionality.\n\n**Related templates:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Shows executed step outputs for runs\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` - Base layout template\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - All styling including DAG visualization\n\n### Key Handler Functions\n\n**Workflow Definition Endpoint:**\n- **`handleAPIWorkflows`** (lines 1058-1132) - Returns JSON with all workflows, steps (with config), and wires for a project. Returns `apiWorkflow` with `apiStepDef` objects containing `Name`, `Type`, `Results`, and `Config` (which holds \"prompt\", \"command\", \"script\" fields).\n\n**Step Content Endpoint:**\n- **`handleAPIStepContent`** (lines 1134-1199) - **This is the key endpoint** that returns the actual prompt/script file contents. It:\n  1. Looks up the workflow by name\n  2. Finds the step in the workflow\n  3. Reads the file referenced in `step.Config[\"prompt\"]`, `step.Config[\"command\"]`, or `step.Config[\"script\"]`\n  4. Returns the content as plain text\n  - Route: `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`\n\n**Step Output Endpoint:**\n- **`handleAPIStepOutput`** (lines 563-634) - Returns captured output from step executions\n  - Route: `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`\n\n### Frontend JavaScript Functionality\n\nIn `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (lines 50-299):\n\n1. **`loadWorkflows()`** - Fetches all workflows from `/api/projects/{name}/workflows` and builds a DAG visualization\n2. **`showWorkflow(idx)`** - Renders the workflow DAG as an SVG with clickable step nodes\n3. **`openDrawer(workflowName, stepName)`** - **Key function** that:\n   - Opens a slide-out drawer panel (lines 251-284)\n   - Displays step metadata (type, results, config keys)\n   - Fetches and displays prompt/script file contents from `/api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`\n   - Renders content in a `<pre>` tag with HTML escaping\n4. **`closeDrawer()`** - Closes the drawer\n\n### Domain Types\n\n**Step Definition** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`):\n```go\ntype Step struct {\n\tName    string\n\tType    StepType\n\tResults []string\n\tConfig  map[string]string  // contains \"prompt\", \"command\", \"script\" keys\n}\n```\n\n**Workflow** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`):\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n\tName      string\n\tSteps     map[string]*Step\n\tWiring    []Wire\n\tCollects  []Collect\n\tEntryStep string\n\tConfig    map[string]string\n}\n```\n\n### Key Files\n\nAbsolute paths to all relevant files:\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - All HTTP handlers\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Workflow DAG and step drawer UI\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Run execution step details\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - Complete styling\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Workflow and Step domain types\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run and StepExecution types"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a3f6de09eb7da1f00 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 58425\ntool_uses: 19\nduration_ms: 22732</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"044f0678-c89a-4054-98f9-8679665edf9d","uuid":"86178195-c2c6-4454-99dc-7eb789a06ea0","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find code related to the workflow view / project page where clicking on steps shows prompt/script filenames. Look for:\n1. Any web UI, frontend, or template files related to workflow visualization\n2. Any handler or endpoint that serves step details or file contents\n3. Code that references \"prompt file\", \"script file\", or step detail display\n\nSearch broadly - check for HTML templates, Go template files, handlers, API endpoints, etc. Look in cmd/, internal/, and any web/ui/static/templates directories.","agentId":"a3f6de09eb7da1f00","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive summary of the findings.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've found all the code related to the workflow view and step details functionality. Here are the key findings:\n\n### Web UI Templates\n\n**Main workflow visualization template:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - This is the **primary file** where the workflow DAG visualization occurs with step detail drawer functionality.\n\n**Related templates:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Shows executed step outputs for runs\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` - Base layout template\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - All styling including DAG visualization\n\n### Key Handler Functions\n\n**Workflow Definition Endpoint:**\n- **`handleAPIWorkflows`** (lines 1058-1132) - Returns JSON with all workflows, steps (with config), and wires for a project. Returns `apiWorkflow` with `apiStepDef` objects containing `Name`, `Type`, `Results`, and `Config` (which holds \"prompt\", \"command\", \"script\" fields).\n\n**Step Content Endpoint:**\n- **`handleAPIStepContent`** (lines 1134-1199) - **This is the key endpoint** that returns the actual prompt/script file contents. It:\n  1. Looks up the workflow by name\n  2. Finds the step in the workflow\n  3. Reads the file referenced in `step.Config[\"prompt\"]`, `step.Config[\"command\"]`, or `step.Config[\"script\"]`\n  4. Returns the content as plain text\n  - Route: `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`\n\n**Step Output Endpoint:**\n- **`handleAPIStepOutput`** (lines 563-634) - Returns captured output from step executions\n  - Route: `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`\n\n### Frontend JavaScript Functionality\n\nIn `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (lines 50-299):\n\n1. **`loadWorkflows()`** - Fetches all workflows from `/api/projects/{name}/workflows` and builds a DAG visualization\n2. **`showWorkflow(idx)`** - Renders the workflow DAG as an SVG with clickable step nodes\n3. **`openDrawer(workflowName, stepName)`** - **Key function** that:\n   - Opens a slide-out drawer panel (lines 251-284)\n   - Displays step metadata (type, results, config keys)\n   - Fetches and displays prompt/script file contents from `/api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`\n   - Renders content in a `<pre>` tag with HTML escaping\n4. **`closeDrawer()`** - Closes the drawer\n\n### Domain Types\n\n**Step Definition** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`):\n```go\ntype Step struct {\n\tName    string\n\tType    StepType\n\tResults []string\n\tConfig  map[string]string  // contains \"prompt\", \"command\", \"script\" keys\n}\n```\n\n**Workflow** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`):\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n\tName      string\n\tSteps     map[string]*Step\n\tWiring    []Wire\n\tCollects  []Collect\n\tEntryStep string\n\tConfig    map[string]string\n}\n```\n\n### Key Files\n\nAbsolute paths to all relevant files:\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - All HTTP handlers\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Workflow DAG and step drawer UI\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Run execution step details\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - Complete styling\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Workflow and Step domain types\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run and StepExecution types"}],"totalDurationMs":22732,"totalTokens":58425,"totalToolUseCount":19,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2793,"cache_read_input_tokens":54646,"output_tokens":981,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2793},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
