{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016oRUjiXR1x9uva1DiuYYDH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All good. Here's a summary of the fix:\n\n**Root cause:** The DSL parser stores prompt/script values in their raw syntax form, e.g. `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")`. The `handleAPIStepContent` handler was using this raw value directly as a file path, so `os.ReadFile` was looking for a file literally named `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")` — which doesn't exist.\n\n**Fix (two parts):**\n\n1. **`handleAPIStepContent`** (`handler.go:1177`): Extract the actual path from `file(\"...\")` wrapper before reading the file, for both `prompt` and `script` config values.\n\n2. **`handleAPIWorkflows`** (`handler.go:1104`): Strip the `file(\"...\")` wrapper from config values sent to the frontend, so the drawer metadata shows clean paths like `.cloche/prompts/implement.md` instead of `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")`.\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":146,"cache_read_input_tokens":28286,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":146},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"044f0678-c89a-4054-98f9-8679665edf9d","uuid":"b7fa59a5-8af4-450a-be34-eeb36c4ba319"}
